Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%grams} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm
wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Sprinkle with the @dried oregano{1%sachet}.
Drizzle with @olive oil{30%ml}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss
to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the middle shelf until golden, ~{30-35%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).
Drain the @sweetcorn{160%grams} in a #sieve{} and pop into a #bowl{}.

Drain and rinse the @black beans{1%carton} in the sieve and pop half of them
into another bowl. Crush the black beans in the bowl using a #potato masher{}.
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%grams}.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Once the
pan is hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%grams} and sweetcorn and cook until
charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during
this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

Once the corn is charred, add the black beans (whole and mashed),
@Central American style spice mix{1%sachet} and garlic to the pan. Season
with @salt{} and @pepper{}, stir well and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Pour in the @water for the beans{75%ml} and @vegetable stock paste{10%grams}.
Stir together, bring to a simmer and cook until the liquid has evaporated,
~{4-5%minutes}.

Remove the pan from the heat, then stir through the cheese. Taste and season
with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

Lay the @super soft tortillas with whole wheat{4} onto a baking tray and spoon
the filling onto one half of each one. Fold the other side over to make a
semi-circle. Press down to keep together.

Drizzle a little oil over the top, then bake on the top shelf of your oven
until golden, ~{8-12%minutes}.

== Salad and Dressing ==

Meanwhile, in a large #bowl{}, combine the @red wine vinegar{12%ml} with the
@sugar{1%tsp} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{}
and @pepper{} and mix to combine.

> Don't add the leaves too early or they'll go soggy.

When the quesadillas are ready, add the @baby leaf mix{20%grams} to the
dressing. Toss to combine.

Divide your quesadillas between plates.

Serve with the herby chips and salad. Add the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} alongside to
finish. Enjoy!